frameDefinitions: The words in this frame involve an Undesirable_event which affects the Patient negatively.
An State_of_affairs will come to hold with respect to a Protagonist at some future time.
An Agent or Cause causes a Process or State to end.
A particular Situation is likely (or unlikely) to result in a harmful event befalling an Asset.
frameExamples: The first <t>calamity</t> was a disastrous trade war with Holland.
Exile was his <t>fate</t> and he triumphantly turned it into the fruit of his life.
Bush may <t>lift</t> sanctions on his own, despite opposition.
listRoleDefinitions: The undesirable event which occurs.
The entity that experiences the <fen>Undesirable_Event</fen>.
When the <fen>Undesirable_Event</fen> occurs.
Where the <fen>Undesirable_Event</fen> takes place.
The <fen>State_of_affairs</fen> that is destined to occur to the Protagonist.

The <fen>Role</fen> filled by the <fen>Protagonist</fen> in his/her destiny.
The time for which the <fen>Protagonist</fen>'s future is determined.
The location in which <fen>State_of_affairs</fen> is destined to occur to the <fen>Protagonist</fen>.
A <fen>Process</fen> which is ended by the <fen>Agent</fen> or <fen>Cause</fen>.
The individual who causes the <fen>Process</fen> or <fen>State</fen> to end.
An event that causes the <fen>Process</fen> or <fen>State</fen> to end.
A <fen>State</fen> which is ended by the <fen>Agent</fen> or <fen>Cause</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Process</fen> or <fen>State</fen> is ended.
The location where the <fen>Process</fen> or <fen>State</fen> is caused to end.
The <fen>Situation</fen> which may lead to a harmful event.
Something judged to be desirable or valuable which might be lost or damaged.
A concrete or abstract entity which may come to cause the loss of, or damage to the Asset.
The time period during which the <fen>Situation</fen> has the specified level of safety.
A particular location for which the <fen>Situation</fen> is safe. Frequently, it is to be inferred that the characteristics of the location make various <fen>Situation</fen>s safe or unsafe.
listRoleExamples: An <fex>environmental</fex> disaster is just what we need.

<fex>That move</fex> ended her political career, she said in a 1994 Times Union interview.
